# MLSECDEVOPS GitLab Pipeline CI -- data quality / drift group.
# Each of these installs in its own per-job venv (great-expectations-validate,
# evidently-drift, ydata-profile, dvc-verify); ydata-profiling in particular pins
# narrow numpy/pandas/matplotlib ranges. If this group cannot resolve as one lock,
# the lockfile-audit job reports a WARNING and these stay covered by the per-job
# .audit-env. See requirements-ci.in for the grouping rationale.
great-expectations
evidently
ydata-profiling
# ydata-profiling breaks on setuptools>=81 (removed pkg_resources APIs it imports at
# runtime); the ydata-profile job pinned this ad-hoc, now folded into the group lock so
# the compiled set matches what the job actually runs. Forces a setuptools downgrade from
# the previously-resolved 82.0.1 — expected on the next recompile.
setuptools<81
# dvc (not dvc[all]): the [all] extra pulls every cloud backend, dragging in
# pydrive2 -> pyOpenSSL 24 (which caps cryptography <44) and oss2/aliyun. The DVC
# job is inert (no remote configured), so the backends are unused weight + the
# pyopenssl/cryptography CVEs. Bare dvc drops that chain with no upgrade risk; add a
# specific backend (e.g. dvc[s3]) only if/when a remote is actually used. diskcache
# (dvc-data, core) has no fixed release and remains — accepted (local-pickle, CI-only).
dvc
